Kima is an asset-agnostic interoperability infrastructure designed to bridge the gap between blockchain networks and traditional financial systems. By providing a unified platform for secure and scalable cross-ecosystem  transactions, Kima enables seamless transfers across different ecosystems, including digital assets and legacy financial systems. Its patent-pending architecture eliminates vulnerabilities associated with smart contracts and key management, ensuring a secure environment for high-volume transactions.
